/*
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
*** T-SQL Chart
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Description:  This script creates stored procedures and functions that turn a 
              given SELECT statement into a chart or a drawing representing 
              selected data. Supports chart types LINE, COLUMN, BAR, PIE, and 
              AREA, and a special type PAINT for free-style drawings.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Authors:      Andrew Zanevsky, Katrin Zanevsky, and Anthony Zanevsky
Email:        zanevsky@azdatabases.com
Version Date: 2011-12-24
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Objects created by this script:
 ----- Basic objects to produce charts and free-style drawings:
 - Chart         The main stored procedure to generate charts and drawings from 
                 a given SELECT query.
 - WKT_Letter    User-defined function to create a WKT string to draw a given 
                 ASCII character.
 - WKT_String    User-defined function to create a WKT string to draw a given 
                 ASCII string.
 - Chart_Colors  Stored procedure to draw a chart of available colors and their 
                 sequence numbers. It is useful to pick unwanted colors for the 
                 @Skip_Colors parameter of the Chart procedure.
 ----- Stored procedures that use objects listed above:
 - Chart_Free_Disk_Space   - Stored procedure to display a pie chart of 
                             currently available free disk space by drive letter.
 - Chart_DB_Size           - Stored procedure to display a column, pie, or bar 
                             chart depicting relative database sizes.
 - Chart_Job_Duration      - Stored procedure to display a line chart of 
                             execution history of a given job.
 - Chart_Job_Step_Duration - Stored procedure to display an area or column 
                             chart of execution history of a given job by step 
                             (shown as separate data series of different colors).
 - Chart_All_Jobs_History  - Stored procedure to display a floating bar chart 
                             depicting execution history of all scheduled jobs 
                             that took longer than a given duration and that 
                             were started within a given time range.
 - Chart_Art               - Stored procedure to create computer-generated art -
                             either generate a random drawing or reproduce a 
                             specific drawing from a given integer seed.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Usage instructions:
   All objects have header comments explaining their purpose and inline comments
   after each parameter explaining its usage and defaults.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Installation instructions:
   Execute this script from a query window in a database where you want to 
   install them. It is sufficient to install these objects in just one database 
   on a particular SQL Server, as they may be used to produce charts based on 
   data selected from any other database on the same server or linked servers, 
   provided that the user executing the procedure has read permissions on 
   objects involved in the given SELECT.
   Note that if objects with the same names already exist in the database, then 
   this script will attempt to alter them and replace with versions found in 
   this script.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
*/

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
